---
description: Conventional commits
alwaysApply: true
---

conventional_commits:
examples: - 'feat(auth): add jwt authentication' - 'fix(api): resolve user creation error' - 'docs(readme): update installation steps'
format: - '<type>(<scope>): <description>' - <summary>
rules: - Use conventional commit format - Keep messages professional and concise - Maximum 72 characters for description - Use lowercase for all text - Use imperative mood (add not added) - Use the summary to describe the changes in a multiples lines
types:
chore: Maintenance tasks
ci: CI/CD related changes
docs: Documentation changes
feat: A new feature
fix: A bug fix
perf: Performance improvements
refactor: Code refactoring
style: Code style changes
test: Adding or updating tests
language_rules:
examples: - '// Good: Calculate total price' - '// Bad: Calculer le prix total' - '// Good: getUserById()' - '// Bad: obtenirUtilisateurParId()' - '// Good: README.md in English' - '// Bad: README.md in French'
format: All code, documentation and comments must be written in English
rules: - All code must be written in English - All documentation (README, docs, etc.) must be written in English - All comments in code must be written in English - All variable names, function names, and class names must use English terms - All commit messages must be written in English
